owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: This ontology defines classes and properties for describing participants, infrastructure, data and services of the Industrial Dataspace.
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: IDS Information Model

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Constraint that refines an Action.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: action refinement

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: References the connector that is affected by the runtime condition change.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: affectedConnector

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: References the participant that is referenced in the participant-related notification messages.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: affected Participant

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The affected resource that is referenced in the resource-related notification messages.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: affected Resource

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: References the Contract Agreement of two parties.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: approved Contract

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Document describing the operations exposed by the endpoint.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: apiDocument

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to a parameter assignment that describes how an artifact has been created.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: artifact parameterization

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Information of the authentication service used by the Connector.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: authInfo

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The standard used by the authentication service that is provided by the Connector.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: authStandard

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An authorization token like JSON Web Token.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Authorization token

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Beginning of an Interval.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: beginning

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Operation bound to a particular protocol endpoint.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: bound operation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: References the Catalog of published or requested resource by this Connector.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: catalog

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Level of certification (based on a combination of requierements, evaluation method etc.)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: certification level

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Certification issued for the given Infrastructure Component.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: component certification

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to a Connector listed in the Broker.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: connector

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Consumer of a Resource or Service that is the subject matter of the Contract. This party may differ from the Assignee specified by the Contract rules.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Consumer

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to a Digital Content (physically or logically) included, definition of part-whole hierarchies.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: content part

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Constraint that refines a (composite) Digital Content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: content refinement

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Standards document defining the given Digital Content. The content is assumed to conform to that Standard.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: content standard

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Detailed type, genre or interpretation of the Digital Content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: content type

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Any type of resource related to the Contract.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Annex to contract

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Equivalent human-readable encoding of this machine-interpretable Contract.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Contract document

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to a Contract Offer defining the authorized use of the Resource.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: contract offer

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Correlated message, e.g. a response to a previous request.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: consumer connector

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Participant responsible for the correctness of the content offered by the InfrastructureComponent.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: curator

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the data type schema of the Representation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Data Type Schema

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the default host that should be used for basic infrastructure interactions, e.g., providing the self description.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Default Host

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Default representation of the content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Default representation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to domain-specific vocabulary used to describe a content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: domainVocabulary

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: End of an Interval.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: end

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Content instance mediated via this individual endpoint (1:1 mapping).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: endpoint artifact

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Network host that exposes resource content and Connector services via this endpoint.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: endpoint host
owl:ObjectProperty.metamodel:explanation: Definition of a Resource Endpoint is by purpose split into an address part (path, topic etc.) and host information used to augment and resolve the address. Such the overall address space is self-contained and may move across hosts. Further, changes of either component (address vs. host) do not affect the other.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Operation bound to te endpoint by means of a protocol binding.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: endpoint operation binding

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Evaluation Facility that performed and issued given Certification
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: evaluation facility

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to a security guarantee that, if used in combination with a security profile instance, overrides the respective guarantee of the given predefined instance.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: extended guarantee

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Holds information when an Operation has failed.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: fault

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to corresponding fault propagation rule.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: fault propagation rule

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Refers to a GeoPoint that is member of a BoundingPolygon.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: geoPoint

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Networked host operated by the Connector in order to serve and consume resource content and services.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: host

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Certification Level transitively implied by given Certification Level of same root type.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: included certification level

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Industry branch covered by the Participant.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: industrial classification

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to an input Parameter (optionaly) used by the Operation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: input

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Parameterizes the input of an Operation with a predefined paramter group.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: input group

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to an instance of given representation, i.e. inline value or file placeholder.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: instance

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Type of the public key.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Key Type

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Natural language(s) used within the content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: language

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The left operand in a constraint expression.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: leftOperand

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Activity that occurs during the lifecycle of the Managed Entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: lifecycleActivity

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Participant responsible for technical maintenance of the InfrastructureComponent.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: maintainer

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to an input Parameter required by the Operation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: mandatoryInput

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Parameterizes the input of an Operation with a predefined mandatory parameter group.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: mandatory input group

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Holds the mandatory result of an Operation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: mandatoryOutput

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Media Type of the Representation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: media type

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A Resource that is part of a Connector, indicating a offering (of, e.g., data).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: offer

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Declares the Operation to access a DataAsset.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: operation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Detailed type, genre or interpretation of the Operation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: operation type

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Holds the result of an Operation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: output

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Declares a member of a ParameterGroup.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: paramGroupMember

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Defines the operator that relates all members of the ParameterGroup.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: paramGroupingOperator

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Parameter which content is being assigned.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: parameter

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Artifact being assigned to parameter.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: parameter artifact

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Content model of a monovalent parameter, i.e. it bounds one value at most.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: parameter content

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Value being assigned to parameter.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: parameter value

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Certification issued for the given Participant.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: participant certification

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to Message Exchange Pattern supported by the operation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: pattern

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The location where the Connector is physically deployed.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: physicalLocation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Commodization option supplied by the model.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: commodization option

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A subset of a ids:VocabularyDataset that contains only the triples of a certain property.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: propertyPartition

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Communication protocol supported by the host.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: protocol

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Provider of a Resource or Service that is the subject matter of the contract. This party may differ from the Assigner specified by the Contract rules.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Provider

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Public Key that has been created for the Component.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Public Key

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The publisher of the resource (which may differ from the sovereign).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: publisher

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This property specifies the language of the query.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: queryLanguage

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Refers to the scope property of a query message, see ids:QueryScope.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: queryScope

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Connector which is the recipient of the message.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: recipient connector

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Refers to the target property of a query message, see ids:QueryTarget.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: recipient scope

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links a policy to the policy template it is derived from.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: refers to policy template

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specifies the reason of the rejection.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: rejectionReason

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Representation of the content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: representation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Standards document defining the given Representation (in contrast to general Resource content). The Representation is assumed to conform to that Standard.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: representation standard

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A Resource that is part of a Connector, indicating a request (of, e.g., data, software,...).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: request

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to the Endpoints serving the resource's content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: resource endpoint

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to the Interface defining Operations supported by the Resource.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: resource interface

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to a Resource (physically or logically) included, definition of part-whole hierarchies.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: resource part

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Sample Resource instance.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sample

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to a security guarantee supported by given profile.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Security guarantee

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The SecurityProfile supported by the Connector.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: securityProfile

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A token representing a claim that the message sender supports a certain security profile.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Security token

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Interface exposed by the Software, e.g. for configuration, data processing etc.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: software interface

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the sort order of a List.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sort order

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The 'owner', i.e. sovereign of the data.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sovereign

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Named spatial entity covered by the Resource.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: spatial coverage

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to a well-known License regulating the general usage of the Resource.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Standard License

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Concrete, materialized content (artifact) which is the subject of the policy statement.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: target

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Abstract content which is the subject of the policy statement.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: target content

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Temporal period or instance covered by the content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: temporal coverage

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Abstract or concrete concept related to or referred by the content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: theme

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the format of the authentication token.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: tokenFormat

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The contract which is (or will be) the legal basis of the data transfer.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: transferContract

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: (Equivalent) variant of given Resource, e.g. a translation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: variant

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Access URL (e.g., http/websocket host, mqtt broker address and port) required for communication using the protocol.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Access URL

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The regular period with which items are added to a collection.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Accrual periodicity

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The 'aud' (audience) claim identifies the recipients that the JWT is intended for.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: aud

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Size of the Artifact in bytes.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: byte size

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Checksum of the artifact
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: checksum

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Version of the content in the payload. Use digits and semantic versioning pattern like MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: contentVersion

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Date of singing the Contract.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Contract date

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Date and time the Contract is requested, offered or expected to end. If omitted, the contract has to be explicitly terminated by any of the parties.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Contract end

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Human-readable text describing the reason for contract rejection.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Contract Rejection Reason

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Date and time the Contract is requested, offered or expected to start, depending on the type of Contract.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Contract start

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Date when the artifact was created, i.e. persisted.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: creation date

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the data type of the Representation.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Data type

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Date coordinate of the instant.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: date

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Date time with a defined time zone.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: date time

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Explanation of the resource in a natural language text.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: description

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Duration of the media resource in seconds.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: duration

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The 'exp' (expiration time) claim identifies the expiration time on or after which the JWT MUST NOT be accepted for processing.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: exp

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Name of the Artifcat file.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: file name

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Suffix of a file name, typically separated by a period, indicating the nature and intended processing of the file.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: filename extension

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Video frame rate.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: frame rate

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Height of the visible frame.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: height

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The 'iat' (issued at) claim contains the point in time when the JWT was created.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: iat

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Data-URL containing the software icon data according to RFC 2397.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Software icon
owl:DatatypeProperty.metamodel:issue: Designing icons as data-URLs makes them 'self-contained', as no referential and resolvable addresses is assumed. This may result in a considerable amount of data enclosed in meta-data annotation.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Information Model version that the InfrastructureComponent is capable of reading/processing.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: inboundModelVersion

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Relative path used for inbound communication via this endpoint, i.e. input messages and faults only.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: inbound topic

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The 'iss' (issuer) claim identifies the principal that issued the JWT.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: iss

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Binary representation of the key.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Key Value

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Controlled keywords that describe the nature, purpose, or use of the content.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: keyword

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Last date the given Certification is considered valid.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: last valid date

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: End of the participant's IDS membership.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: membership end

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Version of the Information Model against which the Message should be interpreted.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: model version

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Entity name unique within a specified context.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: name

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The 'aud' (audience) claim identifies the recipients that the JWT is intended for.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: nbf

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Information Model version being produced by the InfrastructureComponent.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: outbound model version

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Relative path used for outbound communication via this endpoint, i.e. output messages and faults only.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: outbound topic

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Relative path, topic or queue at which the content is published by the related host.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: path

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Prefix optionally prepended to all of the paths served by the host.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: path prefix

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The rdf:Property that is the predicate of all triples in a property-based partition.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: property

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Plain Text containing the reason for revoking an existing certificate of an infrastructure component, e.g. a connector or participant.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: revoke reason

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Audio sampling rate.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: sampling rate

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to SHACL shape graph, which describes domain-specific knowledge.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: shapeGraph

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates an address for the site.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: site address

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The 'sub' (subject) claim identifies the principal that is the subject of the JWT.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: sub

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: (Localized) name of the entity.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: title

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An authentication token value like JSON Web Token.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: tokenValue

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Separate certificates for IDS identification and transport encryption opens an attack vector for relay attacks. In order to prevent these attacks, a binding of this transport certificates to the connector is required. The inclusion of SHA256 fingerprints of currently valid transport certificates, mainly into the DAT, enables the client to relate the transport layer security with the IDS interactions.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: transportCertsSha256

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Version identifier of the Managed Entity
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: version

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to an URI which contains the domain vocabulary.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: vocabulary

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Width of the visible frame.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: width

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message requesting an access token. This is intended for point-to-point communication with, e.g., Brokers.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Access Token Request

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Response to an access token request, intended for point-to-point communication.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Access Token Response

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A thing one might be permitted to do or prohibited from doing to something.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Action

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Something that occurs over a period of time and acts upon or with entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Activity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Internal or external Agent interacting with the Industrial Data Space, not necessarily an IDS Participant.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Agent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of documents describing an API or service contract in a complete and concise way so that it can act as a basis for developing or (automatically) inferring clients.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: API Document Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource control for deployed services.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App execution resources

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Secure platform for distributing Data Apps.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Store

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Instance of a Representation materialized at a partiuclar version and point in time. Possesses characteristics like file name, size, creation date etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artifact

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message asking for retrieving the specified Artifact as the payload of an ArtifactResponse message.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artifact Request Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message that follows up a RetrieveArtifact Message and contains the Artifact's data in the payload section.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artifact Response Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Terminal data nodes, i.e. an atomic, possibly typed scalars.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Atomic data

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Content intended for auditive perception, requires an audio output device (i.e. a loudspeaker) to present the contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Audio

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Audio representation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Audio Representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising audio content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Audio Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Local audit logging (including integrity protection) is the baseline for auditing and clearing. Remote audit log tracing provides means to do external audit verification.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Audit guarantee

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Holds authentication information so that connections to the Connector's data offerings can be establised.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AuthInfo

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of authentication standards that may be supported by Connectors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AuthStandard

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Authentication mechanism applied prior to opening a connection. Examples are the verification server's identity or doing mutual authentication.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Authentication

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Implementation of the Connector specification providing only restricted security capabilities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Base Connector

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of binary operators.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BinaryOperator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Defines an area of interest as a set of connected points.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BoundingPolygon

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Broker holding an index of published data endpoints.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Broker

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: e.g. Paypal, Visa Card
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cash machine

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class that aggregates Resources which, as a whole, form a (distributable) Catalog.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Catalog

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Abstract certification of compliance according to given Certification Scheme.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Certification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Appointed by the International Data Spaces Association the Certification Body manages the certification process, defines the standardized evaluation procedures and supervises the activities of the Evaluation Facilities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Certification Body

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Level of Certification
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Certification Level

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Scheme defining the processes, roles, targets, and criteria involved in the certification of components and entities; maintained by the Certification Body.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Certification Scheme

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is subject to a fee-based use.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Chargeable use

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Clearing House provides clearing and settlement services B2B interactions within the International Data Spaces.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Clearing House

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation allowing the Client for custom pagination of underlying list.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Client paginating operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Group of elements supporting particular access operations based on the concrete subclass.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Collection

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Representation of a Collection, i.e. a Map or List of elements.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Collection representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource comprising a set of named (Map) or ordered (List) elements.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Collection resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Command messages are usually sent when a response is expected by the sender. Changes state on the recipient side. Therefore, commands are not 'safe' in the sense of REST.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Command Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Mutating operation that changes the internal state of the providing component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Command

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Process and result of certifying a software component/servivce in order to become a certified part of the International Data Space infrastructure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Component Certification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Level of a Component Certification
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Component Certification Level

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource comprising multiple Digital Contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Composite Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of categories for classification of Resources.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Concept

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Dedicated communication server for sending and receiving data in compliance with the Connector specification. There are different types of Connectors according to provided capabilities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) about the availability of a new connector. The payload of the message must contain the new connector's self-description.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Available Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Whenever a Connector has been successfully certified by the Certification Body, the Identity Provider can use this message to notify Infrastructure Components.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Certificate Granted Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a (previously certified) Connector is no more certified. This could happen, for instance, if the Certification Body revokes a granted certificate or if the certificate just expires.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Certificate Revoked Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) that a connector will be inactive and most likely be available again in the future.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Inactive Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Superclass of all messages, indicating a change of a connector's conditions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Notification Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) that a connector will be unavailable and never be available again.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Unavailable Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) about a connector's configuration change. The payload of the message must contain the updated connector's self-description.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Update Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of Constraints that restrict a Rule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Constraint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation for receiving data via the operation’s input parameter(s) from the Data Provider to the Data Consumer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Consume content operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is charged based on an effective consumption/demand (as opposed to a flat rate subscription).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Consumption-based pricing

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Container composed of multiple (individually defined) parts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Container

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Container representation, i.e. of a (compressed) archive.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Container representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Enumerated types of content expanding upon the Digital Content hierarchy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Content type
owl:Class.metamodel:usage: Instances of Content Type are used to more precisely specify the type, genre or interpretation of a Digital Content.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Abstract set of rules governing the usage of a Resource.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Contract governing the actual usage of a Resource that has been agreed by all parties.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract agreement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message containing a contract with resource access modalities on which two parties have agreed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract Agreement Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Contract issued by the Data Provider offering the usage of a Resource at particular conditions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract offer

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message containing a offered content contract (as offered by the data provider to the data consumer) in the associated payload (which is an instance of ContractOffer).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract Offer Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating rejection of a contract.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract Rejection Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Contract issued by the Data Consumer requesting the usage of a Resource at particular conditions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract request

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message containing a suggested content contract (as offered by the data consumer to the data provider) in the associated payload (which is an instance of ContractRequest).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract Request Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message containing supplemental information to access resources of a contract (e.g. resource access tokens).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract Supplement Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to generate or produce an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CreationActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A selection of custom media types to be used for data published on the IDS when no IANA type is available.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Custom Media Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Dynamic Attribute Provisioning Service (DAPS) is a component of the Identity Provider and manages and issues the Dynamic Attribute Tokens (DAT), acting as digtial proofs for dynamic attributes of both connectors and participants.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dynamic Attribute Provisioning Service

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Dynamic Attribute Token (DAT) Payload is the JSON Element of any DAT containing the claims of the token bearer. This payload itself is a JSON-LD encoded RDF class with a defined set of attributes. These attributes are iether defined by RFC 7519 or by the IDS Information Model. As a direct consequence of the regardance of the DAT Payload as JSON-LD, *all* DAT Payloads must have exactly one "@context" attribute with the IDS context URI as its value and a "@type" with ids:DatPayload as its value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DAT Payload

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Custom or generic (semi)structured data intended for machine processing, i.e. atomic values or arrangements of data fields (optionally defined by a schema).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Self-contained, self-descriptive software package that is distributed via the App Store and deployed inside a Connector; provides access to data and data processing capa­bilities; the interface of a Data App is semantically described by the IDS Information Model.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataApp

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Script code, algorithm or any other kind of interpreted software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataApp Asset

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Add-on software extending a host Data App with a dedicated capability. The plugin depends on a particular version (range) of the host Data App which governs its integration, configuration and life-cycle.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataApp Plugin

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Data App for a (stateless) processing of digital content according to exposed software interfaces.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataProcessingApp

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Physical representation of (structured) data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising data content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of datatypes for usage by Operation Parameters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Entity described by a minimal textual annotation, i.e. a title and description.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: described

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Entity described semantically.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DescribedSemantically

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Digital content of a particular type providing hints on its usage, e.g. listening to an Audio, navigating a Structure or accessing a List by an index.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Digital content

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of Duties as defined in the ODRL ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Duty

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A JSON Web Token (e.g., for authorization) mediated as part of the message, formerly known as the 'DAPS Token'. The complete JWT *including* header, payload and signiture is referenced by this class and *not* only the JSON element in the payload. See ids:DatPayload for the payload definition.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dynamic Attribute Token (DAT).

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Access point of data exchange and service interaction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Endpoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Evaluation Facilities carry out the evaluation work during a certification process and issue the corresponding Certifications.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Evaluation Facility

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Rules describing the relation and delivery of fault messages, i.e. whether they are omitted, replace or follow a regular operation message.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Fault propagation rule

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is charged based on a selection of features (i.e. map overlays, service set etc.)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Feature-based pricing

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation provides the Data Consumer with a selection of a Collection contents according to supplied Filter Parameter. The Filter is applied to 'structured' Resource content or file properties of Artifatcs (such as file extension, file name, file type, etc.).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Filter content operation
owl:Class.metamodel:rationale: Extends ids:ListContentOperation, since filtering upon entire Digital Contents which definition still applies.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter holding a filter expression (matcher) used to identify a matching selection of contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Filter parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is charged on subscription base independently of the actual consumption.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Flatrate pricing

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is free of charge, its usage is optionally restricted by non-financial constraints.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Free use

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Model that exposes limited parts of the product at no cost, while additional parts are charged.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Freemium model

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A location identified by a geonames URL.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GeoFeature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A location identified by geo coordinates.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GeoPoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Geometrical shape indicating a spatial area of interest.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Geometry

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Network host capable of serving and consuming digital content and services.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Host

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of media types registered with IANA.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: IANA Media Type
owl:Class.metamodel:example: idsc:TEXT_CSV a ids:IANAMediaType; # the retrieved representation (HTML, turtle, RDF/XML) depends on content negotiation owl:sameAs <https://w3id.org/spar/mediatype/text/csv> .
owl:Class.metamodel:usage: Definition of an ids:IANAMediaType should define individual equivalence to corresponding SPAR-Media Type.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter for conveying identifiers as defined by, e.g. an element collection (name/key). The identifier is unique and valid (in a defined context) regardless of the actual extent, ordering, and view (filtering).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identifier parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Identity Provider manages and validates the digital identity of International Data Spaces Participants.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identity provider

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Static content intended for visual perception/interpretation, requires a display device (i.e. a screen) to present the contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Image representation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image Representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising image content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Payment taking place immediately before or simultaneously to product consumption.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Immediate payment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter conveying the transient, positional identifier of a resource in the context of an ordered Collection. The resource index is temporarily unique and valid only with respect to the actual extent, ordering, and view (filtering) of the Collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Index parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of industries that can be distinguished by their activities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Industrial classification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Classification according to International Standard Industrial Classification (ISIC).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ISIC Industrial Classification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of all infrastructure components of the IDS.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: InfrastructureComponent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal entity with zero extent or duration.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Instant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Level of integrity protection and verification of the installed software stack. Trusted boot is an example of local integrity protection, remote integrity verification comprises, for example, remote attestation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Integrity protection and verification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Level/extent of verifying the software stack.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Integrity verification scope

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Endpoint exposing a digital content in a interacitve way.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Interactive Endpoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Conceptualization of the interchange of digital artifacts as a set of uniform operations (interactions primitives).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Interface

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal entity with non-zero extent or duration, i.e. for which the value of the beginning and end are different.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Interval

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message requesting the recipient to invoke a specific operation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Invoke Operation Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Cryptographic Key Type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Key Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of languages potentially being used by textual Data Assets.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Language

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Instances of the LeftOperand class are used as the leftOperand of a Constraint.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LeftOperand

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of Licences to be referred to by Resources.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: License

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter indicating the number of elements retrieved or provided at once within a paginated subset (page).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Limit parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ordered collection of elements allowing for an index-based access.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation used by a Data Consumer to retrieve an enumeration of Collection's contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List content operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation used to retrieve the enumeration of available values for an 'Identifier' Parameter type. Depending on the type of underlying Resource collection, the identifier may be a unique name (map) or a numeric index (list); the Data Consumer may use the identifier for a subsequent call to 'Read' operation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List identifiers

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation exposing a list (ordered collection) of Digital Content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation used by a (potential) Data Consumer to retrieve (a dynamically generated) enumeration of input parameter values (its enumerated value domain); suitable for use cases in which the complete parameter range cannot be specified beforehand.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List parameter values operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Means by which local data is protected.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Local data confidentiality

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of all locations on Earth.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Location

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Log notification which can be used to transfer logs e.g. to the clearing house.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Log Notification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of mutable individuals that are a potential subject to lifecycle management which may need to be tracked.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Managed entity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Collection of elements allowing for a key based access.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Map

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: General class of media types (formerly known as MIME types).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Media Type
owl:Class.metamodel:usage: ids:CustomMediaType is used only when no ids:IANAMediaType available.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Metadata describing payload exchanged by interacting Connectors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Pattern governing the sequencing and cardinality of operation parameters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Message exchange pattern

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Notification that a message has been successfully processed (i.e. not ignored or rejected).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Message Processed Notification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity that sustainably modifies the managed entity, resulting in a new version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ModificationActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Entity that is identifiable within a context by means of a name.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Named

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event messages are informative and no response is expected by the sender.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Notification Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter indicating the absolute offset (number of data elements to skip) within an ordered data Collection. Negative values are bounded at Collections's end (reverse) index.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Offset parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Opaque, not further specified type of custom, binary content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Opaque content

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Building block of an Interface; describes the interaction by defining input, output and error parameters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Mapping of abstract operation signatures onto the concrete structures (e.g., HTTP headers or query parameters).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: operation binding

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating that the result of a former InvokeOperation message is available. May transfer the result data in its associated payload section.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Operation Result Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Enumerated types of operations expanding upon the Operation taxonomy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Operation type
owl:Class.metamodel:usage: Instances of Operation Type are used to more precisely specify the type, genre or interpretation of an Operation.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter conveying the transient, positional identifier of a content page within a server-defined pagination.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Page index parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter conveying a relative reference to a content page within a server-defined pagination.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Page reference parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Participant Information Service (ParIS) provides metadata and relevant information about participants (humans and organizations) in the International Data Spaces.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Information Service

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Named slot of an interface operation i.e., an input, output or fault (exception).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Expression of assigning a value to a parameter without creating an immediate reference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Parameter assignment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of Parameters grouped according to an operator.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Parameter group

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of operators that relate all members of a ParameterGroup.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ParameterGroupingOperator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Stakeholder in the Industrial Data Space, assuming one or more of the predefined roles; every participant is given a unique identity by the Identity Provider.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) about the availability of a new participant. The payload of the message must contain the new connector's self-description.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Available Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Whenever a Participant has been successfully certified by the Certification Body, the Identity Provider can use this message to notify Infrastructure Components.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Certificate Granted Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a (previously certified) Participant is no more certified. This could happen, for instance, if the Certification Body revokes a granted certificate or if the certificate just expires.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Certificate Revoked Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Process and result of certifying an interested party in order to become a certified member of the International Data Space.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Certification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Level of a Participant Certification
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Certification Level

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Superclass of all messages, indicating a change of a particpants's conditions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Notification Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) that a participant will be unavailable and never be available again.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Unavailable Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) that information describing this Participant has changed. This event is mainly intended for information describing the Participant that is NOT a direct subject of the certification process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Information Changed Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Model considering the type and timing of the payment (the effective financial compensation).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Payment model

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of Permissions as defined in the ODRL ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Permission

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of persons (people)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Person

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of templates that describe a certain data usage policy.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Policy template
owl:Class.metamodel:usage: Instances of this class conform to a certain textual representation which they need to indicate via a property.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Payment method requiring a contract allowing the product provider to charge the subscriber.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Post-paid payment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: e.g. prepaid SIM
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pre-paid payment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Overall commodization model composed of options.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Commodization model

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Option of turning a Resource or Service into a product.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Commodization option

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation for processing of digital content via operation’s IO parameter(s).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Process content operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of Prohibitions as defined in the ODRL ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Prohibition

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Set of communication rules by which a Service implements its Interface(s) in order to become invocable.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Communication Protocol

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation for providing a single Resource content via an operation’s output parameter from the Data Provider to the Data Consumer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Provide content operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to bring an entity into an operational state.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ProvisioningActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Public key as used in asymmetric cryptography.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Public Key

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to make available an entity for public or restricted access.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PublicationActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is charged by instances of usage based on a particular metrics (byte size, number of API calls, ports etc.).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quantity-based pricing

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of query languages in which query strings may be formalized.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: QueryLanguage

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Query message intended to be consumed by a component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Query Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Reading operation considered 'safe' by not affecting the state of the provising component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Query

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of scopes that may limit the space of query results, e.g. ALL, ACTIVE_ONLY.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Query Scope

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of recipients of a query message, e.g. BROKER, APPSTORE, ANY.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Query Target

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Rejection messages are specialized response messages that notify the sender of a message that processing of this message has failed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Rejection Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of reasons that might lead to issuing a Rejection message.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RejectionReason

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to decommission an entity so that it can never be used anymore.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RemovalActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Syntactic template of a Resource.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A particular instance of given representation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Representation instance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Notification that a request has been accepted and is being processed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Request In Process Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Client-generated message initiating a communication, motivated by a certain reason and with an answer expected.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Request Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource is a single digital content or a coherent set of digital contents. Resource content is formalized in Representations and optionally materialized as Artifacts. The Resource's content is exposed via defined Interfaces at various protocol Endpoints.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating that a specific resource is available.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Resource Available Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Superclass of all messages, indicating a change of a resource.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Resource Notification Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter conveying a representation of resource's principal content, contrasted to parameters mediating arbitrary data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Resource parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating that a specific resource is unavailable.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Resource Unavailable Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating an update of a specific resource.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Resource Update Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Response messages hold information about the reaction of a recipient to a formerly sent command or event. They must be correlated to this message.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Response Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Result messages are intended to annotate the results of a query command.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Result Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to resume operation of a temporarily suspended entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ResumptionActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Superclass of Permissions, Prohibitions and Duties.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Rule

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising a Schema.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Schema Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Security guarantee claimed by a security profile.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Security guarantee

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Set of security guarantees claimed by a Connector. Connectors may asses their mutual technical reliability and trustworthiness by evaluating each other’s security profile.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SecurityProfile

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation provides the Data Consumer with custom fragments of the original Collection according to supplied 'Selector' Parameter. The Selector is applied to 'structured' Resource content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Select content operation
owl:Class.metamodel:rationale: Extends ids:QueryOperation, since content selection is driven by user-provided logic and can hardly be defined at description time

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter holding a selector expression used to retrieve a subset of a Resource contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Selector parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message requesting the self-description of an Infrastructure Component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Self Description Request

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message containing the self-description of an Infrastructure Component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Self Description Response

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation allowing the Client to navigate list content based on index of Server-defined sections.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Server-side absolute paginating operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation allowing the Client to navigate list content by references to Server-defined sections.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Server-side relative paginating operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Service isolation mechanism supported by the Connector. Examples are process group (Docker) or by least privilege with clear separation and support for additional security modules as done by trustme.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Service isolation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to make an entity unoperational, while retaining it and make it operational again at a later point in time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ShutdownActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource comprising exactly one Digital Content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Simple Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An office or other premise at which the organization is located
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Site

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Executable software (binary), interpreted program code (source) or fragments thereof. Intended purpose is an optional preprocessing (i.e. compilation, installation) and subsequnt execution/invokation of the software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Software
owl:Class.skos:note: Term 'application' was misleading, since Mime Type of same name refers to unspecified data processed by some type of application program.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Software representation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Software Representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising Software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Software Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter indicating the keys underlying the sorting of an ordered Collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sort key parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of possible order methods for collections.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sort Order

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter indicating the sort direction of an ordered Collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sort order parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation allowing for sorting of an underlying List.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sorting operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Anything with spatial extent, i.e. size, shape, or position, e.g., places and unique positions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SpatialEntity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Regulation mandated by a standardization body or set of rules established and followed by a community (de facto Standard).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Standard

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Endpoint exposing an Artifact.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Static Endpoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Custom or standardized structured data
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Structure

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Payment taking on periodical rate according to underlying contract terms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Subscription payment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to temporarily suspend operation of an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SuspensionActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Data Apps that integrate sources and sinks of digital content maintained internally on Participant's premises with a Connector.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: System Adapter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal interval or instant.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TemporalEntity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Informative textual content intended for reading and interpretation by humans and other intelligent agents. Comprises any digital representation of text, e.g. document and image (screenshot).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Text
owl:Class.skos:note: Text generlizes the notion of Media Type 'text' as a meaningful sequence of characters written in a set of human language(s), regardless of the formating and file type (e.g. plain, Word or PostScript).

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Representation of a textual content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Text representation
